commits.message:
Enhance Sidebar and AppRoutes for ticket and report management

- Removed commented-out Profile button from Sidebar for cleaner code.
- Added new Pending Tickets and Reports sections in Sidebar with corresponding NavButtons.
- Introduced routes for Pending Tickets and Reports in AppRoutes, ensuring access control for ADMIN and SUPERVISOR roles.
- Updated ticket navigation to close the sidebar upon selection for improved user experience.

Update package dependencies to include @react-pdf/renderer and related packages

- Added @react-pdf/renderer version 4.3.0 to package.json and package-lock.json.
- Included additional dependencies for @react-pdf components to enhance PDF rendering capabilities.
- Updated package-lock.json to reflect new dependencies and their versions.

Add ReportDetails, ReportList, and ReportPDF components for report management

- Introduced ReportDetails component to display detailed information about individual service reports, including options to edit and delete reports.
- Added ReportList component to manage and display a list of tickets, with search and pagination functionalities.
- Created ReportPDF component to generate and download service reports as PDF documents, enhancing report accessibility.
- Implemented loading states and error handling for improved user experience across components.

Refactor TicketService to enhance ticket management functionality

- Changed the updateTicket method to use PATCH instead of PUT for partial updates.
- Added new endpoints for managing pending tickets, including fetching pending tickets, retrieving a pending ticket by ID, and handling reports associated with tickets (fetching, updating, and deleting reports).
- Improved error handling for new endpoints to provide clearer feedback on failures.

Add CustomSelect and Pending Ticket components for enhanced ticket management

- Introduced CustomSelect component for improved dropdown functionality with custom styles and icons.
- Added PendingTicketDetails component to display detailed information about pending tickets, including status, activity timeline, and options to delete or edit tickets.
- Created PendingTicketsList component to manage and display a list of pending tickets with search functionality.
- Implemented UpdatePendingTicketSection for editing ticket details, including status and assignments, with validation and error handling.
- Enhanced TicketDetails component to improve the display of ticket status changes and activity timeline.

Add gitignore rules for example binaries

Prevent compiled example binaries from being committed to git:
- identity_verification example binary
- health_monitoring example binary
- General example binary patterns

Compiled binaries should never be checked into version control.

performed_via_github_app.name: changeset-bot
performed_via_github_app.description: This bot will comment on PRs saying that either a user might need to add a changeset(note that PRs changing things like documentation generally don't need a changeset)or say that the PR is good and already has a changeset. Sometimes, a contributor won't add a changeset to a PR but you might want to merge in the PR without having to wait on them to add it. To address this, this bot adds a link with the filename pre-filled to add a changeset so all you have to do is write the changeset and click commit. When writing the changeset, it should look something like this with the packages that are being released in the YAML front matter with associated semver bump types and the summary of the changes in markdown. ```markdown --- '@changesets/cli': major '@changesets/read': minor --- A very helpful description of the changes ```

issue.title: 1080p MP4 download often falls back to 640x360
issue.body:
When selecting 1080p video quality and MP4 format, the download does not always retrieve the requested resolution. Most of the time, it pulls a 640x360 video instead.

To get the correct 1080p file, I have to delete the lower-resolution version and retry the download â€” sometimes up to 5 attempts before it finally grabs the 1080p version.

Environment:

* Running latest Docker image (2025.07.31)

* macOS host

Steps to reproduce:

1. Select a video that has 1080p available.

2. Choose 1080p quality and MP4 format.

3. Start download.

4. Check the file resolution â€” often itâ€™s 640x360.

5. Repeat download until 1080p is eventually fetched.

Expected behavior:
When selecting 1080p MP4, the first download should consistently retrieve the 1080p version.

Actual behavior:
Downloads often fall back to 640x360 resolution, requiring multiple retries.

comment.body: @Brodieman It's probably issue with how parameters get passed down to "yt dlp", so when I chose MP4 I'm limited only with 360p, even if I choose other qualities. My rule of thumb is try again with same parameters, if not change between them until I download.

pull_request.title: Add login/signup system (auth.py, users.json) and integrate with streâ€¦
pull_request.body:
Changes Made

Added auth.py: Handles user login and signup logic.

Added users.json: Stores registered user credentials in JSON format.

Updated streamlit_app.py:

Integrated login/signup before accessing app pages.

Blocks access until the user is authenticated.

Why this change?

Improves security by ensuring users must log in before accessing the application.

Lays the foundation for role-based access and personalization in the future.

 How to Test

Run the app with streamlit run streamlit_app.py.

Create a new account via the signup option.

Login with the registered credentials.

Verify that navigation to Home, Stock Dashboard, Finance Bot, Goal Planner is only possible after login.
